                            <comment id="17374214" author="michael-o" created="Sun, 4 Jul 2021 07:50:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With SLF4J or sysout?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17374735" author="tibor17" created="Mon, 5 Jul 2021 10:05:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Actually both slf4j and sysout need to be in one lock. The reason is that the test summary goes through slf4j (normal maven logger - apache api) but the console logs (a user calls System.out.println() in his tests) appear in sysout and syserr.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17374736" author="tibor17" created="Mon, 5 Jul 2021 10:06:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I do not require a fix in Maven. This can be easily done in surefire implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17374784" author="michael-o" created="Mon, 5 Jul 2021 12:07:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your explanation makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376517" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 12:15:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Pls have a look at the log in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1927&quot; title=&quot;JVM exit with Process Exit Code:0 failing builds&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1927&quot;&gt;SUREFIRE-1927&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The guy uses {{ -T 1C}} and there are some fragments of text mixing when the modules run in parallel.&lt;br/&gt;
It is different issue from this but maybe can say if our logger uses Mutex.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376579" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 13:36:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why do you think that this issue will solve the &lt;tt&gt;exit(0)&lt;/tt&gt; issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376763" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 18:18:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Michael, you did not read my comment very properly &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; right? I did not say that the Maven logger and exit(0) is somehow related. No, nothing like that really!&lt;br/&gt;
I only said that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1927&quot; title=&quot;JVM exit with Process Exit Code:0 failing builds&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1927&quot;&gt;SUREFIRE-1927&lt;/a&gt; has an interesting log and the user runs parallel Maven built with {{ -T 1C }} and so that we should look at these fragments because they are looking strange and it looks like parallel modules log the lines and scruble them without Mutex - at least this come the first thing I see in the log therefore I want to hear your impression of the log WDYT about the log?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[ERROR] R] *********.util.json.formatter.JsonFormatterTest
[INFO] --- maven-jar-plugin:2.4:jar (default-jar) @ cloudtrail-cep ---
 [ERROR] Process Exit Code: 0
[ERROR] *********.util.json.formatter.JsonFormatterTest
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376819" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 20:23:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I read your comment therefore the ticket confused me. I have seen &quot;broken&quot; output already before even with just SLF4J (simple). I think one can try a &lt;tt&gt;synchronized(targetStream)&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/qos-ch/slf4j/blob/39e3b81e5ea69c6610c8d5fd57fd974e090d9fc1/slf4j-simple/src/main/java/org/slf4j/simple/SimpleLogger.java#L246-L247&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376823" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 20:27:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See: &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/a/6123321/696632&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/a/6123321/696632&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376826" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 20:32:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shit, it is threadsafe internally: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-jdk8u/blob/9a751dc19fae78ce58fb0eb176522070c992fb6f/jdk/src/share/classes/java/io/PrintStream.java#L521-L538&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-jdk8u/blob/9a751dc19fae78ce58fb0eb176522070c992fb6f/jdk/src/share/classes/java/io/PrintStream.java#L521-L538&lt;/a&gt; Maybe talk to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ceki%40qos.ch&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ceki@qos.ch&quot;&gt;ceki@qos.ch&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17376843" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2021 20:58:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=michael-o&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;michael-o&quot;&gt;michael-o&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Let&apos;s switch to Slack, because our talks may confuse the users of Jira. I found something...maybe the cause.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
